race.comment: AIRSWING (2) switched yards this preparation and improved sharply second-up when narrowly beaten at Glen Innes over 1400m. The extra 100m will suit and he's still well shy of his best. Maps for the run of the race and can go one better. SOMETHING FORJO (5) was a comfortable Toowoomba winner three back over this trip and has been around the mark there both starts since. The inside gate is against but she's suited and the runs should come. ARDUOUS (6) resumes and has switched to Jack Bruce from a top Sydney stable. She races forward and her NSW form over this trip reads well. Has two solid Doomben trials under the saddle and she's likely to race well. HURRICANE ROSIE (4) resumes and will race over further. She trialled well and may be presented forward this time around. Has a handy 3kg claim and look for her late. ELEANOR NANCY (7) maps well and can show more third-up. KWT is a positive jockey engagement replacing the apprentice.
